        pour 240 grams of water, give it a short stir, steep for around 90 seconds, then press gently. The cup comes out clean,
        sweet, and easy to read. If something tastes off, you can usually tell whether it needs a finer grind, cooler water,
        or a little more steep time.
      </p>
      <p>
        That clarity is the big win. Paper filters keep the body lighter than metal-filter recipes, so fruit notes and sweetness
        show up without a muddy finish. It is not the boldest AeroPress cup possible, but it is the most dependable all-rounder.
        Honestly, if you only ever use one method, this is the one.
      </p>
